<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Uttar Pradesh</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">Heart of <em>Bharat's Soul</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Uttar Pradesh is not merely a state — it is the living archive of India's entire civilizational memory. From the ghats of Varanasi where Shiva is said to reside, to the birthplace of Lord Ram at Ayodhya and Lord Krishna at Mathura, UP holds more sacred geography per square kilometre than anywhere else on earth. The Taj Mahal at Agra — a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the Seven Wonders of the World — draws visitors from every nation. Prayagraj hosts the Kumbh Mela, the largest peaceful gathering of human beings in recorded history, where over 50 million pilgrims converge at the Triveni Sangam. Lucknow's Nawabi culture of tehzeeb, Benares's ghats alive with Sanskrit chants at dawn, Agra's Mughal magnificence and Vrindavan's Krishna devotion create a tapestry of culture unmatched anywhere in the world. With 75 districts, 240 million people and 5,000 years of continuous history, Uttar Pradesh is where India's past lives and its future is written.</p>
</section>

